Einstein Work Summaries

You want your bot to reflect your company's brand, which means you must consider the language and tone your bot uses.

In a contact center, agents get trained on the company-specific ways to address customers. And guess what? You can “train” your bots to sound like your agents instead of like machines.

Customizing your initial greeting, you can make your bots sound like your company from the get-go.

This plays out in more detailed ways. One key thing you write when building your bots are bot’s messages. They can be customized to match your company’s voice and tone.

Want some more ideas? Check out how we at Salesforce create our voice in our Writing Style Trailhead module, and our corporate style guide.
title: Personalizing Einstein Bots with Company Branding
